snippet.textDisplay:
Some people think that the Sith scare the Jedi, and to an extent, they do fear the Sith, but they're enemies, and they understand them.

It's pretty basic to think that the Jedi may be more fearful of monstrosities and horrors they had never faced even during the times of the Old Republic and beyond. The Sith have been their enemies for multiple millennia, they're an artistic clash of two ideologies, aggression and altruism at their purest forms. They aren't as fearful of the Sith as they are spiteful since they want to seemingly 'restore balance to the force' by ridding away the Sith as a whole when really Light cannot exist without Dark. So really when you think about it, the Sith and Jedi, if they came to more common ground had potential to become polar-opposite allies, since both their methods when it comes to war and politics work in their own unique ways.

The point I wish to convey is that it's a misunderstanding, believing the Jedi actually fear the Sith when they truely see them as a rival, and also in some instances, potential allies. The unknown is what both the Sith and Jedi truely fear deep down, as if they cannot understand or do not know the threat, then they cannot retaliate against them, and finish that battle, that clash of power and attunement with the weapons they built naturally.

tl;dr the sith and jedi don't actually fear each other, but rather the unknown, and so i believe it's a pretty common misunderstanding that they do.

Very hopeful for the series, loved some of the novels by Drew Karpyshyn, hope this does just as well as those ones!

This is a good step towards the light side tbh. Disney, in my opinion, cut too much fat from Star Wars. Then they added new worlds, characters, stories, and villains which made it stop feeling like Star Wars.

I think Star Wars is at it's best when you're seeing established things in a new way. Like Tatooine being a recurring planet or the adventures of Anakin and crew in Clone Wars.

High Republic offers that because we get to see established things, the Jedi and the Republic, in a new light.
